data.enText: close envelope
to close an envelope, etc. by sticking the edges of the opening together

data.chText: 一定要在支票上签了名再封信封。
data.enText: Make sure you've signed the cheque before sealing the envelope.
a sealed bid (= one that is kept in a sealed envelope and therefore remains secret until all other bids have been received)
close container
to close a container tightly or fill a crack, etc., especially so that air, liquid, etc. cannot get in or out

data.chText: 这些器官保存在密封塑料袋里。
data.enText: The organs are kept in sealed plastic bags.
cover surface
to cover the surface of sth with a substance in order to protect it

data.chText: 地板上东西挪空，涂上了清漆。
data.enText: The floors had been stripped and sealed with varnish.
make sth definite

data.chText: 确定；明确定下来；使成定局
data.enText: to make sth definite, so that it cannot be changed or argued about
to seal a contract

data.chText: 他们干了一杯，交成朋友。
data.enText: They drank a glass of wine to seal their new friendship.

data.chText: 新发现的证据决定了他的命运。
data.enText: The discovery of new evidence sealed his fate (= nothing could prevent what was going to happen to him) .
close borders/exits
to prevent people from passing through a place

data.chText: 军队已关闭了两国边界。
data.enText: Troops have sealed the borders between the countries.
my lips are sealed

data.chText: （表示不会说出某人的秘密）我把嘴封住，我绝口不提

official mark
an official design or mark, stamped on a document to show that it is genuine and carries the authority of a particular person or organization
The letter bore the president's seal.
making sth definite

data.chText: 表示确认的事物；保证；信物
data.enText: a thing that makes sth definite

data.chText: 项目已由政府正式批准。
data.enText: The project has been given the government's seal of approval (= official approval) .

data.chText: 我把你的礼物看作我们之间友谊的见证。
data.enText: I looked upon the gift as a seal on our friendship.
on containers
a substance, strip of material, etc. used to fill a crack so that air, liquid, etc. cannot get in or out

data.chText: 盖子上有密封垫的广口瓶
data.enText: a jar with a rubber seal in the lid

data.chText: 只喝瓶装水，并且要看封口开了没有。
data.enText: Only drink bottled water and check the seal isn't broken.
on letters/boxes

a piece of wax (= a soft substance produced by bees ), soft metal or paper that is placed across the opening of sth such as a letter or box and which has to be broken before the letter or box can be opened

data.chText: 他揭去封蜡，把纸卷展开。

a piece of metal, a ring, etc. with a design on it, used for stamping a wax or metal seal

value.def: When you seal an envelope, you close it by folding part of it over and sticking it down, so that it cannot be opened without being torn.

example.ex: He sealed the envelope and put on a stamp...
example.tran: 他封住信封并贴上一张邮票。

example.ex: Write your letter and seal it in a blank envelope...
example.tran: 信写好后把它装进空白信封里封好。

example.ex: A courier was despatched with two sealed envelopes.
example.tran: 信使受命递送两封封讫的信。

value.def: If you seal a container or an opening, you cover it with something in order to prevent air, liquid, or other material getting in or out. If you seal something in a container, you put it inside and then close the container tightly.

example.ex: She merely filled the containers, sealed them with a cork, and pasted on labels...
example.tran: 她只是装满容器，用软木塞封住，然后贴上标签。

example.ex: A woman picks them up and seals them in plastic bags.
example.tran: 一个女人把它们捡起来放入几只密封的塑料袋中。

example.ex: ...a lid to seal in heat and keep food moist.
example.tran: 用于保温并防止食物风干的盖子

example.ex: ...a hermetically sealed, leak-proof packet.
example.tran: 密封防漏的包装

value.tran: 封住(容器、开口);把…密封(进容器)

value.def: The seal on a container or opening is the part where it has been sealed.

example.ex: When assembling the pie, wet the edges where the two crusts join, to form a seal.
example.tran: 在包馅饼时，先把两片馅饼皮边沿接头部分弄湿，再将其捏合。

value.def: A seal is a device or a piece of material, for example in a machine, which closes an opening tightly so that air, liquid, or other substances cannot get in or out.

example.ex: Check seals on fridges and freezers regularly.
example.tran: 定期检查冰箱和冷冻柜的密封装置。

value.def: A seal is something such as a piece of sticky paper or wax that is fixed to a container or door and must be broken before the container or door can be opened.

example.ex: The seal on the box broke when it fell from its hiding-place...
example.tran: 盒子从隐藏处掉落时，封口裂开了。

example.ex: Protestors banged on the sides of the lorry and broke customs seals on the doors.
example.tran: 抗议者们猛砸卡车的侧面，并且撕掉了车门上的海关封条。

value.def: A seal is a special mark or design, for example on a document, representing someone or something. It may be used to show that something is genuine or officially approved.

example.ex: ...a supply of note paper bearing the Presidential seal...
example.tran: 一批盖有总统印章的便条纸

example.ex: The best wines are entitled to a numbered seal of quality.
example.tran: 上等葡萄酒可以盖上带编号的优质产品印章。

value.def: If someone in authority seals an area, they stop people entering or passing through it, for example by placing barriers in the way.

example.ex: The soldiers were deployed to help paramilitary police seal the border...
example.tran: 部署士兵协助准军事警察封锁边境。

example.ex: A wide area round the two-storey building is sealed to all traffic except the emergency services.
example.tran: 那个两层建筑周围的大片区域被封锁，只有提供应急服务的车辆可以通行。

example.ex: Police and troops sealed off the area after the attack...
example.tran: 袭击发生后警察和士兵将该区域封锁。

example.ex: Soldiers there are going to seal the airport off.
example.tran: 那里的士兵将封锁机场。

value.def: To seal something means to make it definite or confirm how it is going to be.

example.ex: McLaren are close to sealing a deal with Renault...
example.tran: 麦克拉伦即将与雷诺达成一笔交易。

example.ex: A General Election will be held which will seal his destiny one way or the other...
example.tran: 一场决定他命运的大选即将举行。

example.ex: His artistic character was sealed by his experiences of the First World War.
example.tran: 他在第一次世界大战中的经历奠定了他的艺术风格。

value.def: If something sets or puts the seal on something, it makes it definite or confirms how it is going to be.

example.ex: Such a visit may set the seal on a new relationship between the two governments...
example.tran: 这样的一次访问可能会使两国政府间确立新关系。

example.ex: They see this election as a chance to put the final seal on the defeat of communism.
example.tran: 他们把这次选举看作是彻底击败共产主义的一次机会。

value.def: If a document is under seal, it is in a sealed envelope and cannot be looked at, for example because it is private.

example.ex: Because the transcript is still under seal, I am precluded by law from discussing the evidence.
example.tran: 副本仍未公开，按照法律规定我不能讨论这项证据。

value.tran: 盖上印信的;不能拆开看的;保密的

value.def: A seal is a large animal with a rounded body and flat legs called flippers. Seals eat fish and live in and near the sea, usually in cold parts of the world.
